caption: I have officially become a regular because of how much I love this place. A cute setting, European vibes, and it’s just a perfect little cafe. The food is good & the crepes are immaculate. Highly recommend to everyone.

Love this place! I had actually discovered the place around 2 years ago on door dash when I ordered in lunch while at work. I loved the food then but since it wasn't super close to where I live, I only had it once but then forgot about it. Well I have recently been working in the area and was looking for places to have lunch. I saw Iguana Cafe on the map and immediately recognized the name and remembered how much I loved the food the last time that I had it. I ordered for pick up this time and, again, it did not disappoint. This time I had the opportunity to view the place. It is really welcoming inside and the staff is very friendly. The food is delicious and reasonably priced. I recommend the spinach pesto pasta or the spicy chicken pepper wrap (If you like spicy food).
Great Crepes! Still one of my favorites. My friends and I made it a weekly habit to go there and have crepes. Honestly, I lived in 3 states and it is still the best.
Love this place! Cozy cafe with excellent food and great service. Definitely a hidden gem and the pesto pasta is a must have!

Love this place so much! Amazing crepes and European style cafe drinks. Service is great and the atmosphere is cozy. I always share a savory and a sweet crepe with my fiance. This is definitely one of our favorite places.

There are not enough great things to write about Iguana Cafe! I’ve been coming here for years and now some of my favorite memories are those I’ve had sitting in the cafe. By far some of the best crepes in the city. Love the European and the “where everybody knows your name” vibe as I’m sure some of the staff would be able to put my order in without even asking! Please support Iguana so I can keep eating crepes!

Iguana Café has always been a go to spot for me and my wife since the beginning of our relationship. As a result, we reached out to them to see if they would be willing to do a restaurant buyout for our rehearsal dinner. They agreed, and we are so glad they did! Yanni and Sophia were extremely accommodating and their communication was great. During the event, all our guests raved about the food, service, and ambiance. Simply put, we couldn't have been happier with our rehearsal dinner experience. One of our favorite spots in Chicago for the past six years!

The food is delicious, they have a variety of things to choose from the menu. The crepes are HUGE and are loaded with toppings. You get your money's worth. This place is honestly a hidden gem in Chicago.

Overall, my dinner at Iguana Cafe was enjoyable. The restaurant has a laid-back atmosphere with dim mood lighting. It seems to be set up for one-on-one dates primarily, though I saw a couple larger groups in the upper seating area. I ordered the Mac + Cheese w/ bacon and mushrooms and the Chicken Pesto sandwich. The Mac + Cheese was delicious, really flavorful and savory. The sandwich was decent, but besides the chicken being tender and juicy, it really lacked flavor. It tasted like a functional on-the-go meal more than something I’d receive at a sit-down restaurant. Still, the atmosphere, service, and Mac + Cheese made the experience really nice.
